Kairosoft games have a way of making time pass as if you were trapped in a stasis and the rest of the world goes on without you.  I wish I could say it were pure hyperbole in that their games could have you playing for hour upon hour upon hour, but it isn't.  Sushi Spinnery was the first Kairosoft game I'd gotten, and it became a game I couldn't put down. I found it quite fun to be designing my sushi restaurant, designing sushi combinations while thinking, 'would these flavors mesh IRL', and working hard to keep the money flowing and trying to make the perfect combo that would satisfy the next sushi competition, (where one entrant presenting an empty plate and dubbed it 'air sushi'. Lazy or brilliant? Still not sure.)  As you try to make the perfect layout, you have to work on your sushi chefs and increasing their capabilities so they can make you money, put effort into balancing flavors, keep your customers happy, make sure you have enough chefs for each conveyor setup, and so on.  I found it all wonderfully engaging, and as someone with a high interest in all things culinary, creating sushi was fun as heck.  Worth $4.99? Yes. Definitely. I've paid more for less in other games.

Set the buffet specials and combine ingredients and items to make spots and specials. If they were to make a casino game and incorporate all the awesomeness that has appeared in all the prior games I would pay $10 for it! #2. A monster breeding and supply game. (breed the monsters to make new ones and sell them. #3. An amusement park sim. Create rides and increase the fun factors!     I am a customer for life! Just make a casino sim with some playable tables. That would ROCK! My favorite ones so far are Sushi Spinnery, Mega Mall Story, Epic Astro Story and Dungeon Village. Keep it up Kairosoft!
